%I A385523 #26 Jun 06 2026 09:35:59
%S A385523 2,4,5,8,9,16
%N A385523 Numbers that are not cycle counts of inseparable graphs.
%C A385523 Since subdividing edges does not change the inseparability or the cycle count, the sequence holds equally for simple graphs and multigraphs.
%H A385523 Ryan McCulloch, Brendan D. McKay, Alireza Salahshoori, and Thomas Zaslavsky, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00373-026-03047-3">The Cycle Counts of Graphs</a>, Graphs and Combinatorics 42:53, (2026). See p. 2; <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2507.02260">arXiv:2507.02260</a> [math.CO], 2025.
%Y A385523 Cf. A385524 (cubic graphs).
%K A385523 nonn,fini,full
%O A385523 1,1
%A A385523 _Thomas Zaslavsky_, Jul 01 2025
